01:48:28,01 --> 01:48:31,01
从此就一直想赎罪
And I've been trying to buy it back ever since.

1709
01:48:31,05 --> 01:48:35,55
你和对方达到共识吗？
But you and this mystery man, you have an understanding?

1710
01:48:35,72 --> 01:48:39,56
应该有，他把信封带出去
I think so. And he managed to get out of there with that envelope.

1711
01:48:40,60 --> 01:48:43,94
有一天他会勒索你
If someday he comes back to blackmail you, well,

1712
01:48:44,77 --> 01:48:47,48
你会付钱把信封拿回来
you'll pay him. And you'll get it back.

1713
01:48:48,73 --> 01:48:50,82
-就这么简单 -我猜也是
-So, I guess that's it. -I suppose so.

1714
01:48:50,90 --> 01:48:52,78
-放屁 -你说什么？
-Bullshit. -I beg your pardon?

1715
01:48:52,86 --> 01:48:56,74
他大费周章不是为了你的信封
He didn't go through all that just to stick your envelope under his mattress.

1716
01:48:56,78 --> 01:48:59,62
他们一毛钱都没拿
Look, they left money untouched, Arthur.

1717
01:48:59,70 --> 01:49:00,83
又怎样？
So?

1718
01:49:00,91 --> 01:49:05,29
他一定有拿走什么
So, he had to have walked out of there with something else.

1719
01:49:06,25 --> 01:49:08,75
银行说什么都没被拿走
The bank says that there was nothing missing.

1720
01:49:08,84 --> 01:49:11,42
你的保险箱
So, there had to have been something in that box

1721
01:49:11,51 --> 01:49:14,13
一定有更值钱的东西
that was worth more to him than your envelope.

1722
01:49:16,14 --> 01:49:18,14
你不必告诉我
You don't have to tell me.

1723
01:49:18,22 --> 01:49:20,60
不过只有一个可能
There's only one thing it could be anyway.

1724
01:49:23,98 --> 01:49:25,56
钻石
Diamonds.

1725
01:49:26,11 --> 01:49:27,94
还有一只
And then there's the ring.

1726
01:49:28,65 --> 01:49:30,40
卡地亚钻戒
Cartier ring.

1727
01:49:30,69 --> 01:49:33,65
它属于一位巴黎银行家夫人
It belonged to the wife of a Parisian banker.

1728
01:49:34,07 --> 01:49:36,74
有钱的法国犹太家族
Wealthy family of French Jews.

1729
01:49:37,41 --> 01:49:40,54
战争爆发后，他们的财产被纳粹没收
And when the war came along, the ring and everything else they owned

1730
01:49:40,62 --> 01:49:45,42
全家被送到集中营，无一幸免
was confiscated and they were shipped off to concentration camps. None survived.

1731
01:49:47,46 --> 01:49:49,21
我们是朋友
We were friends.

1732
01:49:49,96 --> 01:49:51,96
我可以帮助他们
I could have helped them.

1733
01:49:53,72 --> 01:49:58,51
但是纳粹党给的条件太好
But the Nazis paid too well.

1734
01:50:00,47 --> 01:50:05,02
我能信任你会对这件事
Can I trust that you will keep what you've learned

1735
01:50:05,10 --> 01:50:08,44
守口如瓶吗？
here today confidential?

1736
01:50:09,48 --> 01:50:11,78
不管你怎么想
Despite whatever you may think?

1737
01:50:20,91 --> 01:50:22,54
没问题
Yes, Arthur.

1738
01:50:24,29 --> 01:50:27,46
我也很想骂你是个人渣
Well, I'd love to tell you what a monster you are,

1739
01:50:27,67 --> 01:50:31,80
不过我要替宾拉登的侄子买公寓
but I have to help bin Laden's nephew buy a co-op on Park Avenue.

1740
01:50:36,01 --> 01:50:38,51
如果是真的你就不会告诉我
If that were true, you wouldn't tell me.

1741
01:50:38,80 --> 01:50:41,01
我会把你列为他的担保人
We're listing you as a reference.

1742
01:50:55,44 --> 01:50:57,78
我的名字是道顿・罗素
My name is Dalton Russell.

1743
01:50:58,36 --> 01:51:00,16
请仔细听我说的话
Pay strict attention to what I say

1744
01:51:00,24 --> 01:51:03,87
因为我要说的话很重要，而且不会重覆一次
because I choose my words carefully and I never repeat myself.

1745
01:51:03,95 --> 01:51:06,66
我说出了名字，那是我的身份
I've told you my name. That's the "who."

1746
01:51:07,71 --> 01:51:11,38
我在的地方可以形容为囚房
The "where" could most readily be described as a prison cell.

1747
01:51:11,92 --> 01:51:13,50
但是被困在一个小囚房
But there is a vast difference

1748
01:51:13,59 --> 01:51:17,13
和坐牢有很大的不同
between being stuck in a tiny cell and being in prison.

1749
01:51:18,84 --> 01:51:21,05
我做了什么事很容易解释
The "what" is easy.

1750
01:51:21,47 --> 01:51:26,18
最近我策划并执行一起完美的银行抢案
Recently I planned and set in motion events to execute the perfect bank robbery.

1751
01:51:27,23 --> 01:51:29,19
我也说出了时间
That's also the "when."

1752
01:51:30,15 --> 01:51:34,53
至于为什么，除了很明显的财务动机
As for the "why," beyond the obvious financial motivation,

1753
01:51:35,23 --> 01:51:37,24
原因其实非常简单
it's exceedingly simple.

1754
01:51:37,40 --> 01:51:39,32
因为我办得到
Because I can.

1755
01:51:39,95 --> 01:51:42,24
现在只剩下我是怎么办到的
Which leaves us only with the "how."

1756
01:51:43,03 --> 01:51:46,04
就像大文豪莎士比亚说的
And therein, as the Bard would tell us,

1757
01:51:47,12 --> 01:51:49,08
这就耐人寻味了
lies the rub.

1758
01:52:37,80 --> 01:52:41,43
-他一定会臭得要命 -一星期没洗澡当然会臭
-He's gonna smell like shit. -What do you expect after a week?

1759
01:52:43,80 --> 01:52:45,26
是啊
Yeah.

1760
01:52:45,30 --> 01:52:47,81
所以我才摇下车窗
Why do you think I rolled down the window?

1761
01:53:07,49 --> 01:53:09,04
糟糕
Oh, shit.

1762
01:53:14,17 --> 01:53:16,75
费警探和他的搭档走进银行
That cop, Frazier, and his partner are walking into the bank.

1763
01:53:16,84 --> 01:53:20,13
-他们来找我吗？ -不确定，只有他们俩
-Are they coming for me? -Can't say. It's just the two of them.

1764
01:53:27,76 --> 01:53:30,72
一切都没事
Yeah, everything's going great today. No.

1765
01:53:31,10 --> 01:53:34,06
对，五点半
Yeah, about 5:30. Okay.

1766
01:53:34,52 --> 01:53:37,06
听起来很好玩
Sounds like fun. Okay.

1767
01:53:37,86 --> 01:53:39,57
待会再聊
Talk to you later.

1768
01:54:00,80 --> 01:54:02,76
-对不起 -抱歉
-Sorry. -Excuse me.

1769
01:54:05,88 --> 01:54:07,26
韩先生？
Mr. Hammond?

1770
01:54:07,34 --> 01:54:09,10
早安，警探
Good morning, Detectives.

1771
01:54:12,68 --> 01:54:14,23
完全按照他的计划
Just like he planned.

1772
01:54:14,31 --> 01:54:16,90
我有搜票打开保险箱
I got a court order here to open a safe deposit box.

1773
01:54:16,98 --> 01:54:18,90
392号保险箱
Number 392.

1774
01:54:30,12 --> 01:54:31,87
谢天谢地
Oh, thank God.

1775
01:54:37,62 --> 01:54:39,33
在哪里？
Where is it?

1776
01:54:39,79 --> 01:54:41,25
我留下来了
I left it in there.

1777
01:54:41,34 --> 01:54:43,05
这里请
This way, Detectives.

1778
01:54:43,09 --> 01:54:45,72
你把钻戒留给谁？
Why did you do that? You left the ring.

1779
01:54:45,76 --> 01:54:47,38
相信我
Trust me.

1780
01:54:47,97 --> 01:54:49,72
对方很可靠
I left it in good hands.

1781
01:54:50,55 --> 01:54:52,31
我不是烈士
I'm no martyr.

1782
01:54:52,85 --> 01:54:54,60
我是为了钱
I did it for the money.

1783
01:54:56,27 --> 01:54:59,81
不过我也要对得起自己的良心
But it's not worth much if you can't face yourself in the mirror.

1784
01:55:00,77 --> 01:55:03,40
良知比金钱更重要
Respect is the ultimate currency.

1785
01:55:06,24 --> 01:55:10,16
我偷一个没有良知的人的钱
I was stealing from a man who traded his away for a few dollars.

1786
01:55:12,08 --> 01:55:14,54
他想用金钱洗清罪恶
And then he tried to wash away his guilt.

1787
01:55:15,66 --> 01:55:19,71
靠做善事获得尊重
Drown it in a lifetime of good deeds and a sea of respectability.

1788
01:55:20,50 --> 01:55:22,63
-让我来 -我自己来
-Let me get that. -Let me.

1789
01:55:22,71 --> 01:55:24,09
他也几乎成功了
It almost worked, too.

1790
01:55:24,17 --> 01:55:25,76
好吧
Okay.

1791
01:55:27,38 --> 01:55:28,93
然而
But inevitably,

1792
01:55:29,72 --> 01:55:32,01
你愈想逃避充满罪恶的过去
the further you run from your sins,

1793
01:55:32,72 --> 01:55:35,68
过去总有一天会追上来
the more exhausted you are when they catch up to you.

1794
01:55:36,02 --> 01:55:37,18
让你自食其果
And they do.

1795
01:55:37,27 --> 01:55:39,02
黄箭口香糖

1796
01:55:39,10 --> 01:55:40,60
好小子
Son of a bitch.

1797
01:55:40,69 --> 01:55:42,31
一定会
Certain.

1798
01:55:42,90 --> 01:55:44,86
这是不变的真理
It will not fail.

1799
01:55:46,74 --> 01:55:48,49
卡地亚-巴黎-伦敦-纽约

1800
01:55:48,99 --> 01:55:50,95
你猜这值多少钱？
What do you think that's worth?

1801
01:55:51,24 --> 01:55:53,91
你问我，你绝对买不起
If you got to ask, man, you can't afford it.

1802
01:55:53,99 --> 01:55:56,37
幸好我女朋友不在
Thank goodness my girlfriend ain't here.

1803
01:55:56,45 --> 01:55:58,41
跟着钻戒走

1804
01:55:58,50 --> 01:56:00,46
“跟着钻戒走？”
"Follow the ring"?

1805
01:56:14,35 --> 01:56:17,27
-费警探 -寇先生
-Detective Frazier. -Mr. Case.

1806
01:56:17,47 --> 01:56:19,48
-你好吗？ -好得很
-How are you? -I am great.

1807
01:56:19,85 --> 01:56:23,27
银行没死人，皆大欢喜，我超爽的
Nobody got killed at the bank. Everybody's happy. My kind of day.

1808
01:56:23,36 --> 01:56:25,32
太好了
That's wonderful. Wonderful.

1809
01:56:25,40 --> 01:56:27,15
-米警探 -寇先生
-Detective Mitchell. -Mr. Case.

1810
01:56:27,19 --> 01:56:29,19
-两位请坐 -谢谢你
-Be seated, gentlemen. -Thank you.

1811
01:56:29,24 --> 01:56:31,53
-喝点什么吗？ -不了
-Can I offer you anything? -No.

1812
01:56:31,61 --> 01:56:33,20
老实说
I must say

1813
01:56:33,57 --> 01:56:36,04
我很佩服
I was most impressed

1814
01:56:37,20 --> 01:56:39,08
你们处理这件事的方法
by the way you handled that business.

1815
01:56:39,16 --> 01:56:40,50
谢谢夸奖
Thank you, Mr. Case.

1816
01:56:40,54 --> 01:56:42,50
你们真的是
Whenever I hear the term "New York's Finest"

1817
01:56:42,54 --> 01:56:44,29
人民保姆
you're who I think of.

1818
01:56:44,38 --> 01:56:47,63
保护平民老百姓的安全
You keep the rest of us safe and make it look easy.

1819
01:56:49,92 --> 01:56:52,30
-不好意思 -有什么好笑？
-Pardon me. -Well, what's so amusing?

1820
01:56:52,38 --> 01:56:55,35
你说平民老百姓，看看你自己
When you say "the rest of us," Mr. Case, I mean, you got to look around.

1821
01:56:55,39 --> 01:56:59,48
你应该不算是平民老百姓吧
"The rest of us" is a category that you haven't qualified for in a long time.

1822
01:56:59,56 --> 01:57:02,27
说的好，我的确很成功
Touche, Detective. I won't deny it. I've done well.

1823
01:57:02,35 --> 01:57:04,52
没错，不过我搞不懂
Yes, you have. But I'm very confused.

1824
01:57:04,56 --> 01:57:06,36
这件案子
You see, I got a case

1825
01:57:07,07 --> 01:57:10,07
抢匪占据你的银行
where armed robbers laid siege to your bank.

1826
01:57:10,11 --> 01:57:11,45
那是你的银行，对吧？
It is your bank, right?

1827
01:57:11,53 --> 01:57:13,41
我是银行董事长
Well, I'm Chairman of the Board of Directors.

1828
01:57:13,49 --> 01:57:15,20
然后…
Then ita-zita-vene-gazoo.

1829
01:57:15,24 --> 01:57:17,20
抢匪从人间蒸发
The robbers disappear. Poof.

1830
01:57:17,53 --> 01:57:18,91
一毛钱都没拿走
And they don't take a nickel, right?

1831
01:57:18,99 --> 01:57:21,33
-你在问我？ -对，我在问你
-You're asking me? -Yes, I'm asking you.

1832
01:57:21,41 --> 01:57:23,58
这是你的银行，我当然要问你
I mean, it's your bank. You own it. I'm asking you.

1833
01:57:23,67 --> 01:57:25,58
那只是我的企业的一小部份
It's a tiny part of our organization.

1834
01:57:25,63 --> 01:57:27,75
没有抢案、没有受害者，也没有丢掉一毛钱
No robbers. No real victims. No loot missing.

1835
01:57:27,84 --> 01:57:29,92
这一定是史上头一遭
It's got to be the first time in law-enforcement history.

1836
01:57:30,01 --> 01:57:31,17
我没听过这种怪事
I never heard of it before.

1837
01:57:31,26 --> 01:57:34,30
你一定会想，这是怎么回事？对不对？
So, you got to ask yourself, "What the fuck happened?" Don't you, Mr. Case?

1838
01:57:34,39 --> 01:57:36,01
我不喜欢你的语气
I'm not quite sure I like your tone, Officer.

1839
01:57:36,10 --> 01:57:38,43
不喜欢的话就说实话
You don't like my tone? Then give me a straight answer.

1840
01:57:38,51 --> 01:57:42,35
那是你开的第一家银行，也是你的心血结晶
It's the founding bank of your empire. You built it. It's your baby.

1841
01:57:42,43 --> 01:57:44,48
老实说，发生什么事？
Give me a straight answer. What do you think happened?

1842
01:57:44,56 --> 01:57:48,19
-我不知道 -少来这一套
-I have no idea. -Oh, come on, now. Come on.

1843
01:57:48,27 --> 01:57:49,69
让我告诉你吧
I'll tell you what I think happened.

1844
01:57:49,78 --> 01:57:51,90
你派那个女人搞定一件事
I think you sent that woman in there to patch things up.

1845
01:57:51,99 --> 01:57:54,53
你付钱请魏小姐办事，她替你办什么事？
Miss White. I think you paid her. What was she doing in there?

1846
01:57:54,61 --> 01:57:56,07
这太荒谬了
Look, this is absurd.

1847
01:57:56,16 --> 01:57:58,12
你在暗示我和抢案有关？
Are you implying that I had anything to do with it?

1848
01:57:58,05 --> 01:57:59,68
392.

1849
01:58:00,37 --> 01:58:02,87
392号保险箱是怎么回事？
Safe deposit box 392. What's the story on that?

1850
01:58:02,91 --> 01:58:05,54
392号
-I have no idea what you're... -Don't lie to me, Mr. Case.

1851
01:58:02,96 --> 01:58:05,33
-我不知道你在说什么？ -别想骗我

1852
01:58:05,42 --> 01:58:07,92
-我没有说谎 -我查过所有记录
-I don't lie. -I looked at all the records.

1853
01:58:07,96 --> 01:58:11,55
银行的每一个保险箱记录
All the bank records for safe deposit boxes at your bank.

1854
01:58:11,71 --> 01:58:14,43
乍看之下没有问题
At first glance, everything looked fine,

1855
01:58:15,18 --> 01:58:17,51
但是有一个保险箱没有记录
but there was one safe deposit box that had no records.

1856
01:58:17,59 --> 01:58:19,56
从1948年起就没有记录
I mean, going all the way back to 1948.

1857
01:58:19,64 --> 01:58:22,77
我在想谁能解开这个谜？
So I started thinking. Who would have the answer to this riddle?

1858
01:58:22,85 --> 01:58:24,73
一定是1948年
Probably the man who forgot to mention

1859
01:58:24,81 --> 01:58:27,10
成立银行的人
that he built the bank in the first place in 1948.

1860
01:58:27,19 --> 01:58:29,94
这整件事都不对劲
It doesn't add up, Mr. Case. It does not add up.

1861
01:58:30,98 --> 01:58:35,28
我恐怕帮不了你的忙
I'm afraid I can't be of any further use to you, Detective.

1862
01:58:36,45 --> 01:58:38,95
你想隐藏一件可怕的秘密
It's something really bad, isn't it?

1863
01:58:39,66 --> 01:58:44,29
我一辈子都为社会奉献
Mr. Frazier, I have spent my whole life serving humanity.

1864
01:58:45,75 --> 01:58:47,79
你可以问我的朋友
You can ask anyone who knows me.

1865
01:58:49,08 --> 01:58:52,09
他们都会替我说好话，我做了太多善事了
They'll vouch for me, and for the things that I've done.

1866
01:58:52,17 --> 01:58:55,22
我查出这只钻戒的真相，他们还会替你说话吗？
You think they'll vouch for you after I find out the truth about this ring?

1867
01:58:55,30 --> 01:58:57,05
应该不会吧
I don't think so.

1868
01:59:01,35 --> 01:59:04,39
你说我们是人民保母
Oh, by the way, that thing you said about us being New York's finest?

1869
01:59:04,48 --> 01:59:07,10
多谢夸奖
I want you to know, we really appreciate that.

1870
01:59:07,73 --> 01:59:09,48
你真是客气
How gracious.

1871
01:59:09,90 --> 01:59:12,57
走吧，咱们要跟着钻戒走
Let's go. We're gonna follow that ring.

1872
01:59:19,57 --> 01:59:22,16
-老兄，让我看你的鞋子 -什么？
-Hey, Keith, let me see your shoe. -What?

1873
01:59:22,20 --> 01:59:24,62
-让我看你的鞋子 -为什么？
-Let me see your shoe. -Why?

1874
01:59:24,70 --> 01:59:27,92
你狠狠地踩到那老家伙的痛处
'Cause I have never seen anybody put their foot that far up a guy's ass.

1875
01:59:30,83 --> 01:59:32,50
我猜是吧
Yeah, I guess I did, didn't I?

1876
01:59:32,59 --> 01:59:35,17
你把他踩到无地自容
Oh, man. You cut him an ass the length of the Lincoln Tunnel.

1877
01:59:35,26 --> 01:59:37,59
他巴不得想挖个洞钻进去
We're gonna need a traffic cop on that shit.

1878
01:59:46,52 --> 01:59:47,68
您好
Good afternoon, sir.

1879
01:59:47,77 --> 01:59:49,69
-您有订位吗？ -我来找市长
-Do you have a reservation? -Looking for the Mayor.

1880
01:59:49,73 --> 01:59:51,73
-请把帽子给我 -不行，你自己去买
-May I have your hat, please? -No, you cannot. Get your own.

1881
01:59:51,81 --> 01:59:54,40
他们要在四年内投资四十亿
They're looking to invest $4 billion over the next four years.

1882
01:59:54,48 --> 01:59:55,65
资金都到位了
And that's all in place.

1883
01:59:55,73 --> 01:59:58,70
市长先生，抱歉打扰了，不过有句美国名言说…
Sorry to interrupt you, Mr. Mayor, but there's an old American saying,

1884
01:59:58,74 --> 02:00:02,53
“只要街头喋血，就会有人坐牢”
"When there's blood on the streets, somebody's got to go to jail."

1885
02:00:03,20 --> 02:00:06,20
请你离开一下
Edwin, could you please excuse us for a minute?

1886
02:00:08,29 --> 02:00:09,87
有什么事？
What's this about, Detective?

1887
02:00:09,96 --> 02:00:13,50
费警探想要一个圆满结局
I believe Detective Frazier is looking for some closure?

1888
02:00:13,84 --> 02:00:16,09
说的好，圆满结局
That's a good word. Closure.

1889
02:00:16,17 --> 02:00:18,76
我要结案，了吗？
Case closed, you know what I mean?

1890
02:00:18,84 --> 02:00:20,18
这是
This is the number

1891
02:00:20,26 --> 02:00:24,30
华府战争罪调查局的名片
of the War Crimes Issues office in Washington, D.C.

1892
02:00:25,93 --> 02:00:28,56
你想登上『纽约时报』头版吗？
How'd you like to be on the front page of the New York Times?

1893
02:00:28,60 --> 02:00:29,73
棒呆了
That'd be great.

1894
02:00:29,81 --> 02:00:33,15
确定他们写对我的名字，费雪
Make sure they spell my name right, though. That's Frazier with a "z".

1895
02:00:34,27 --> 02:00:36,19
录音笔留着吧
You can keep the pen.

1896
02:00:36,53 --> 02:00:38,40
你有拷贝吗？
You made copies?

1897
02:00:39,61 --> 02:00:41,20
放心吧
Please.

1898
02:00:41,28 --> 02:00:44,66
我得去抓真正的罪犯
We got to keep the real criminals off the streets, Your Honor.

1899
02:00:46,12 --> 02:00:48,79
好了，多谢请客
All right, well, thanks for lunch.

1900
02:00:53,17 --> 02:00:54,88
战争罪？
War crimes, huh?

1901
02:00:55,54 --> 02:00:57,76
这次你把我扯进什么事？
What have you got me into this time?

1902
02:01:17,36 --> 02:01:18,98
宝贝？
Mama?

1903
02:01:23,16 --> 02:01:25,91
-你回来了 -还带了一鸟二石
-Did you bring Big Willie? -And the twins.

1904
02:01:39,55 --> 02:01:40,80
别急
Slow down, girl.

1905
02:01:40,88 --> 02:01:43,26
我先把枪放下再掏另一把枪
I'll get my gun off before I get my gun off, okay?

1906
02:01:43,34 --> 02:01:44,80
砰
Pow, pow.

1907
02:01:52,64 --> 02:01:56,86
费基斯升任为高级警探

1908
02:02:26,55 --> 02:02:28,55
-对不起 -抱歉
-Sorry. -Excuse me.

1909
02:02:29,01 --> 02:02:31,68
-你何不走出大门？ -我会的
-Why don't you just walk out the door? -I will.

1910
02:02:32,06 --> 02:02:34,94
我准备好就会大摇大摆走出去
I'm gonna walk out of that door when I'm good and ready.

1911
02:02:35,02 --> 02:02:36,65
好家伙
Son of a bitch.

1912
02:02:43,69 --> 02:02:46,57
快点啦，手铐都冰了
Come on, honey. The handcuffs are getting cold.

1913
02:08:35,38 --> 02:08:36,34
剧终

